I"¾<p>Heroku is a container-based cloud Platform as a Service (PaaS). Developers use Heroku to deploy, manage, and scale modern apps. The platform is elegant, flexible, and easy to use, offering developers the simplest path to getting their apps to market. <a href="https://ionicframework.com/docs/api/menu" target="_blank">Read more from ionic framework docs</a></p>

<p>This tutorial will teach you how to deploy your rails 6 app ot heroku.
The guide assumes that you:</p>
<ol>
  <li>are using linux ubuntu as your OS ()</li>
  <li>are using postgres as your appâ€™s database</li>
  <li>have opened an account with heroku</li>
</ol>

<p>Lets begin:</p>

<p>1). Install heroku CLI</p>

<p>Open the terminal and issue the command below</p>

<h1 id="1-install-heroku-cli">1. Install heroku CLI</h1>
<section class="terminal-container terminal-fixed-top">
<header class="terminal">
<span class="button red"></span>
<span class="button yellow"></span>
<span class="button green"></span>
user@local_machine
</header>

<div class="terminal-home">
<p class="console">sudo snap install --classic heroku</p>
<p class="console">sudo apt upgrade</p>

<h5 class="hashed"># Remove unused kernels to free up the space from /boot partition</h5>
<p class="console">sudo apt autoremove</p>

<p class="console">sudo reboot</p>   
</div>
</section>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> To obtain the url, you can navigate to the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">app-routing.module.ts</code> and check the path of each page inside the Routes array. Ion icons name values are available on <a href="https://ionicons.com/" target="_blank">ionicons site</a>.</p>

